com.att.research.xacml.api

Interface MissingAttributeDetail

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    JaxpMissingAttributeDetail, StdMissingAttributeDetail, StdMutableMissingAttributeDetail

    public interface MissingAttributeDetail
    Defines the API for objects that represent XACML MissingAtributeDetail elements as part of a Status element. MissingAttributeDetails relay information back about the reason a policy decision may have failed due to the absence of required AttributeValues.
    Version:
    $Revision: 1.1 $
    Author:
    Christopher A. Rath

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean equals(java.lang.Object obj)
      Implementations of the MissingAttributeDetail interface must override the equals method with the following semantics: Two MissingAttributeDetails (m1 and m2) are equal if: m1.getCategory().equals(m2.getCategory()) AND m1.getAttributeId().equals(m2.getAttributeId()) AND m1.getDataTypeId().equals(m2.getDataTypeId()) AND m1.getIssuer() == null && m2.getIssuer() == null OR m1.getIssuer().equals(m2.getIssuer()) AND m1.getAttributeValues() is pairwise equal to m2.getAttributeValues()
      Identifier getAttributeId()
      Gets the Identifier representing the XACML AttributeId of the Attribute that was missing.
      java.util.Collection<AttributeValue<?>> getAttributeValues()
      Gets the Collection of AttributeValues that were expected for the Attribute that was missing.
      Identifier getCategory()
      Gets the Identifier representing the XACML Category of the Attribute that was missing.
      Identifier getDataTypeId()
      Gets the Identifier representing the XACML DataType of the AttributeValue that was missing.
      java.lang.String getIssuer()
      Gets the String representing the XACML Issuer for the Attribute that was missing if required.

      • getAttributeValues

        java.util.Collection<AttributeValue<?>> getAttributeValues()
        Gets the Collection of AttributeValues that were expected for the Attribute that was missing. If there are no expected AttributeValues this method should return an empty list. The Collection returned should not be modified. Implementations are free to use unmodifiable Collections to enforce this.
        Returns:
        a Collection of AttributeValues that were expected for the Attribute that was missing.
